{
    "id": "electronics/basic-circuit",
    "title": "Build a basic LED circuit",
    "description": "Learn the basics of circuits by wiring an LED with a current-limiting resistor on a breadboard.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/basic_circuit.svg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Hey there! I'm Orion. We'll light a 5 mm LED with a 220 Ω Resistor on a Breadboard. Keep the 5 V Power Supply unplugged and use the resistor color chart with verify-resistor-color-code to confirm the resistor value before wiring.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "Sure, what do I need?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "Gather a Breadboard, two Jumper Wires, a 5 mm LED, a 220 Ω Resistor, the resistor color chart, and a 5 V Power Supply. Leave the supply disconnected while wiring to avoid shorts. Ready to assemble?",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble",
                    "text": "Yep, let's assemble it.",
                    "process": "verify-resistor-color-code",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 2
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "48cf736e-184c-4bd1-b9b0-15b7e9721646",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "037e6065-68a7-4ad1-9b0b-7778ecfe0662",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "bf3d2784-d48d-4b12-b12a-75f563b5dc88",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "828d6c3b-66a5-4064-b221-97630274502b",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "assemble",
            "text": "Insert the 5 mm LED into the Breadboard with its long leg (anode) toward the positive rail. Place the 220 Ω Resistor from that anode row to an empty row. Use Jumper Wires to link the resistor to +5 V and the LED's short leg to ground. Check that the resistor is in series, the LED polarity is correct, and nothing bridges the power rails. After verifying connections, plug in the 5 V supply and the LED should glow.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "It works!"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Great job! You've built your first circuit and lit an LED. Disconnect power before changes and keep metal tools away from the rails.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Thanks, Orion!"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
